## Phase 3: The API Authentication Journey (The 3 Keys)

The most significant architectural layer of this project was setting up the upstream AI processing engine. We explored three separate paradigms, dealing with pricing mechanics, local hardware constraints, and production model deprecation.

### The Core Paradigm: Why Input the Key via UI?

> **Security Best Practice:** Hardcoding keys or structural authorization passwords directly into source code repos is a catastrophic security vulnerability. If pushed to public GitHub files, scraping bots will steal them within seconds. By collecting the key dynamically using Streamlit's `st.sidebar.text_input(type="password")`, the token lives purely in short-term local browser memory and is never exposed in the source code.

```
       [ Local Browser Session ]
                   │
         (Enter API Key in UI)
                   │
                   ▼
  [ Streamlit app.py Engine (Local) ]
                   │
     (Transmits Payload + Key via HTTPS)
                   │
                   ▼
       [ Cloud LLM Endpoint API ]

```

| Attempt | Target Model / Engine | Authentication Method | Result / Error Faced | Resolution & Architectural Lesson |
| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |
| **1** | OpenAI `gpt-4o-mini` | Developer Secret Token (`sk-...`) | **Error 429: Insufficient Quota** | **Lesson:** Monthly consumer subscriptions (ChatGPT Plus) are entirely separated from developer API programmatic access. The API is pay-as-you-go and requires independent credit allocations. |
| **2** | Ollama (Local `llama3`) | Decoupled Localhost Loop (`http://localhost:11434`) | **Hardware/Resource Constraints** | **Lesson:** Local LLMs offer free, fully private data compliance, but require massive local CPU/GPU resource overhead and storage limits that can throttle execution speed. |
| **3** | Google AI Studio `gemini-1.5-flash` | Free Tier Cloud Token | **Error 404: Model Not Found** | **Lesson:** Cloud models are constantly under active lifecycle management. Passing an outdated string name calls an endpoint that has been deprecated or moved by the provider. |
| **Final** | Google AI Studio `gemini-3.5-flash` | Free Tier Cloud Token | **Success (201 Created)** | Successfully generated complete, professional Markdown RCA documents using a free tier, enterprise cloud engine. |

