## Reference Manual: Commands & Terminology

### 1. System Engineering Glossary

* **SRE (Site Reliability Engineering):** A discipline that incorporates software engineering aspects into information technology operations problems to build highly scalable and reliable software systems.
* **RCA (Root Cause Analysis):** A structured problem-solving method used to identify the exact technical failure point that triggered an outage, preventing recurrence.
* **MTTR (Mean Time to Repair):** The average time required to troubleshoot, fix, and restore a failed system component to active service.
* **API (Application Programming Interface):** A software intermediary that allows two separate programs (e.g., your local web tool and Google's AI brain) to safely speak to each other.
* **Endpoint / Base URL:** The explicit web address where a web service lives and listens for incoming programmatic requests.

### 2. Linux & Command-Line Cheat Sheet

| Command | Action Performed | Context in This Project |
| --- | --- | --- |
| `cd [directory]` | Changes current shell directory path. | Navigated directly into the `ai-rca-generator` folder. |
| `ls` | Lists files in the current folder path. | Confirmed `app.py` was saved in the right spot. |
| `nano [file]` | Opens terminal-native text editor. | Created and altered the source code sheets directly. |
| `Control + C` | Sends an interrupt signal (SIGINT). | Killed the running Streamlit server to free up the command line. |
| `Control + K` | Cuts/Deletes an entire line of text inside Nano. | Cleared out the corrupted syntax markdown code instantly. |
| `Control + O` | Writes out (Saves) changes inside Nano. | Saved the code into the physical storage blocks. |
| `Control + X` | Exits the Nano application interface. | Safely returned to the active terminal prompt loop. |

